Dollar, Yen Gain Versus Euro as Shares Slide, Before Data on U.S. Prices

-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 
2011-08-18T01:27:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/dollar-yen-gain-versus-euro-as-shares-slide-before-data-on-u-s-prices.html
The dollar and yen gained against
most major counterparts as Asian shares extended losses and
before data today on U.S. consumer prices.  The U.S. currency climbed to $1.4408 as of 10:25 a.m. in
 Tokyo  from $1.4426 in  New York  yesterday. The yen climbed to
110.38 from 110.50.   The MSCI Asia Pacific Index declined 0.6 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candice Zachariahs in Sydney at 
